SUMMARY:Mocktails & Meaning™: Artificial Intelligence in Education
DESCRIPTION:Be part of our March Mocktails & Meaning™ gathering as we welcome Dr. Oliver Dreon\, Professor of Educational Foundations at Millersville University\, for a timely conversation on Artificial Intelligence in Education. With more than thirty years in public education and experience teaching at the middle school\, high school\, undergraduate\, and graduate levels\, Dr. Dreon brings a broad and thoughtful perspective on how technology is reshaping classrooms and learning. Together\, we’ll explore the opportunities\, challenges\, and big questions AI is raising for students and educators alike. We’ll be sipping a refreshing Pineapple and Cucumber Juice mocktail while we engage this important topic\, with time set aside for questions and discussion. \nRegister By Clicking Here
URL:https://apostlesucc.org/event/mocktails-meaning-artificial-intelligence-in-education/
LOCATION:Church of the Apostles UCC\, 1850 Marietta Ave\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17603\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://apostlesucc.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Mocktails-Meaning-Flyer-Banner-Landscape-1-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
